Happy National Siblings Day! 👧🏻👦🏻👧🏻. Miss being with you guys and laughing nonstop 24/7, even though I facetime you guys literally everyday 😂. .
.
Now that we’re all grown up, I love that our bond is stronger than ever. I will always appreciate the group chat we have where we talk about everything and anything, no matter how inappropriate and crazy the conversations may get.  I love the inside jokes we have and how we laugh any time they are brought up.  I love the secrets we tell each other, but keep from mom and papa😗🤫. I love that our family is extremely open and that we laugh at EVERYTHING. You 2 are the only other people who understand just how crazy our family truly is.
.
Thank you, for always being there for me whenever I need someone to laugh with or for someone to listen. I mean you guys have no choice but listen cause I always force you to anw LMAO🤣. But love you both always❤️ after all this thing...let’s go on trip winkwink* 😉😁 thank you @vangvs  and @krataips in advance for sponsoring HAHAHA #neontheme

Saddle up cowboy there’s a new boy in town! Please welcome the very cool Euphorbia ingens Cactus to the Fox family. I absolutely love this tall lad. I’ve been dying to get a large cactus for some time now and finally got one yay! I think this may the the start of a long love affair collecting large Cacti as well as my tropicals. Space in my house may become a big issue hahaha. 
Euphorbia ingens is a species of plant in the genus Euphorbia and the family Euphorbiaceae. It is native to dry areas of southern Africa. It is popularly known as the "candelabra tree", and its milky latex can be extremely poisonous, and a dangerous irritant so me careful me dears. 🌱🦊 #plantasticmrfox 🦊🌱 #cactus #euphorbiaingens #boyswithplants .

//Caption//
Different people have different ideas about love.
Some need flesh and pleasure,
while others need comfort and few kind words.
Just because your idea differs from the crowd 
it does not mean that it is absurd.

Love can be anything and everything.
It can be the sound of someone‘s laughter.
It can be the taste of your morning coffee. 
It can be your rising heartbeat 
when your special one enters the room.
It can be your mother’s lullaby 
which is still echoing in a small corner 
of your tiny heart.

Love can be anything and everything.

It is okay 
if your idea of love seems silly and absurd.

After all,
a silly love 
creates the most mesmerizing butterflies...✨
~ @priyakannan.offl

Uno dei più grandi talenti della scuola russa 🔥

caption.text:
“Lui non era una meteora, non era un frammento di chissà quale corpo celeste come potrebbero essere tanti, lui era a tutti gli effetti una cometa.

Le comete hanno questa particolarità di lasciarsi dietro una luce capace di sedurti, rimani stupito perché ti rendi conto di quanto l’universo calcistico sia vasto, un hotel pieno di stanze ancora da perlustrare, con talenti pregiati ancora da scovare.

La Russia l’ho sempre notata come un terra lontana sopratutto calcisticamente, non molti giocatori russi riuscivano a manifestare il proprio talento fuori dalle mura domestiche, ma lui, lui era un’altra cosa..
Sono sicuro che in Russia non vedevano un attaccante così da Oleh Blochin, la grande stella polare di una prodigiosa Dinamo Kiev degli anni 70/80.
Un paragone degno di nota.

Dal 2009 al 2012 su Fifa era di consueto prendere l’Arsenal, quella fu la squadra che mi toccò profondamente e che ancora rimembro:
Portiere: Almunia.

Difensori: Sagna; Vermaelen; Koscielny; Clichy.

Centrocampisti: Fàbregas; Rosický; Nasri.

Attaccanti: Walcott; Van Persie; Arshavin.

Ci volle poco tempo per farmi innamorare perdutamente con un rammarico che c’è ancora adesso, di aver visto quel talento dissolversi in una nuvola di polvere.

The Soviet Prince.💫”

𝗥𝗜𝗚𝗛𝗧 𝗡𝗢𝗪 
Is the time to ℙℝ𝕀𝕆ℝ𝕀𝕋𝕀𝕊𝔼 𝕆𝕌ℝ 𝕄𝔼ℕ𝕋𝔸𝕃 ℍ𝔼𝔸𝕃𝕋ℍ
Confront what stresses or drains you,
identify what does & doesn’t make you happy. Prioritise what does make you feel content. If you come out of all of this a little more calm & connected to yourself you will have achieved more than any new skill or PB that you could have gained.

𝗥𝗜𝗚𝗛𝗧 𝗡𝗢𝗪 
Is the time 𝔽𝕆ℝ 𝔸ℙℙℝ𝔼ℂ𝕀𝔸𝕋𝕀𝕆ℕ
Of our health, our front line workers, the NHS, our favourite coffee shop or hangout.  The hugs & time spent with loved ones.  The freedom we have always taken for granted to go & do what we want every single day. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

caption.text:
I remember doing this shoot mid February. The bride was in her 40s. She was a widow and it was her 2nd marriage. It was a reception shoot and her Nikkah had taken place an year ago. Her kids were on the shoot too and her husband made sure she was treated like the queen she was. In our meeting prior the shoot day, the woman said something which made me really sad and depicted the mind-set our society carries. She said I’d love for my pictures to be posted on social media but the reason I would rather not do it is because people are going to troll my husband for his cute little gestures, his love and for him marrying me. ⁉️
“What?” ⁣
“Why?”, I asked in utter shock. She said that's what happened when our Nikkah shoot was posted online. People started calling us names because I was older than him, because I had kids and he had never married and yet he treated me exactly how a gentleman should treat his wife. Due to her privacy concerns, the shoot was never posted. ⁣
⁣
But here’s to all the trollers & here’s to men who continue to raise the bar despite all odds. Good on you! ⁣
⁣
It's sunnah⁣
1. It’s sunnah to marry older women.⁣
2. It’s sunnah to marry a divorcee.⁣
3. It’s sunnah to marry a widow.⁣
4. It’s sunnah to help women in household chores i.e. cooking, cleaning, washing etc.⁣
5. It’s sunnah to put food with your hand in your wife's mouth as an expression of love. (graded as a form of charity)⁣
6. It’s sunnah to verbally express love, appreciation, and respect to your wife.⁣
7. It’s sunnah to forgive her mistakes.⁣
8. It’s sunnah to keep yourself looking pleasant for your wife.⁣
9. It’s sunnah to try to know the feelings of your wife and console her when she needs it.⁣
10. It's sunnah to be playful with your wife and spend quality time having fun together. (racing, story-telling, sharing happy occasion with her are some well-known examples)⁣
11. It's sunnah to recline and relax in your wife's lap.⁣
12. It's sunnah to call your wife with beautiful names.⁣
13. It's sunnah to not disclose her private matters to other family members or friends.⁣
14. It's sunnah to love and respect her parents.⁣ P.S this picture is NOT from that shoot. 
#fatimaarifphotography

caption.text:
It's Easter weekend 🐣🐰
______
How would you normally spend your Easter ? And do you eat a lot of chocolate bunnies ? 😋
______
We have this fun tradition in Poland called 'Wet Monday' on Easter Monday ! 💦
We are allowed to splash water at anyone around even if we don't know them ! Older people usually stay home to be safe than wet 🙈 while I myself got thrown into a river TWICE, two years in succession, when I was in Poland on a visit on that day 😅😭
Anything goes on Wet Monday so be sneaky or be wary ! 🙈
💭 Do you have any Easter traditions ?

caption.text:

_________
I could spend hours under this beautiful cherry blossom tree - have you ever been there? The location is 𝒮𝓉𝒶𝓃𝓁𝑒𝓎 𝒞𝓇𝑒𝓈𝒸𝑒𝓃𝓉, in the Notting Hill area.
I managed to take this picture just two days before I self isolated on March the 16th 🙏🏻
The flowers were starting to bloom, I just can imagine how gorgeous is this tree right now. 🌸😔
Spring is my favorite season in London and I miss this city so much.

Me, sat on a log, social distancing (of course) and catching my breath.  Thinking, feeling and breathing in the beauty of one of my favourite places 😌 •
•
Gentle reminder that it’s okay to feel things, even things that we would rather not. You can’t heal what you do not let yourself feel. •
•
Why? When we resist, ignore, minimise, judge, deny or criticise our emotions, it makes them stronger and bigger. We may escape them for a while, but they come back.
•
•
No, we can’t stop the hard stuff from showing up in our lives but we can make it slightly easier if we learn to tolerate those harder emotions, work through them and allow them to pass.
•
•
Yes this takes practice but you can take as long a you need and start over as many times as you need. It is all progress. 💫

#youvegotthis #energy #feelings #youcanthealwhatyoudontfeel #healing #youareenough #youarenotalone #selfcare #selflove #authentic #reflections #bekindtoyourself

preview_comments.text: 📚I got this book for my birthday.  I plan to read the book.
@beth.bonini I haven't seen the film, gonna go see if I can find it.

caption.text:
There are a lot of fairy tale tropes in this book - the wicked stepmother, the ‘Hansel and Gretel’ brother and sister forced to wander in the wilderness, the castle-like home under a spell of enchantment - and perhaps that is why it felt ‘just right’ to me during this strange, surreal time.
*
A lot of people have been discussing appropriate reading material for the #coronavirustimes . . . some favour the dystopian, while others want the comfort of children’s classics or the escapism of fantasy.  I have decided that books which features houses as the main characters suit my mood.  Perhaps it’s because a house can be both a place of refuge and a prison.
*
Full review on Goodreads.
*
Happy #floralfriday to you!
*

caption.text:
“But Still We Laugh.”
I drew this last month, haven’t had a chance to put it on Instagram. I did however a couple of weeks ago put a IGTV video up of this drawing. Drawing to me is a meditation. I don’t doodle, all my work is pre-planned and thought through before I create it. Black & white can be as powerful as colour. You are continually working the void of light trying to perfect form. This drawing is my take on how we should confront fear mongering. During this covid-19 outbreak there’s been plenty of fear mongering. So, the best solution to fear is laughter. The best solution to anything or anyone negative is laughter❤️💙😂🙏🏻 #dylangillart #drawing #blackandwhite #artistsoninstagram #emergingartist #portraitdrawing #abstractart #art #arte #arttherapy #happiness #laughterisgoodforthesoul #artwork #artoftheday #artnow #modernart #contemporaryart #contemporaryartist #contemporary_art

caption.text:
Happy Good Friday everybody! 🐣💛
Here’s a simple little Easter bake from the @fitwafflekitchen 👩‍🍳
Mini Egg Millionaire’s Shortbread! 😍
.
Sound on for full instructions 🔉
.
Here’s the ingredients:
200g Softened Butter
100g Caster Sugar
275g Plain Flour
300g Mini Eggs (crushed)
1 tin Carnation Caramel
300g Melted Chocolate
.
That’s it 🙌
Easy and perfect for the Easter weekend 🥰
#fitwafflekitchen #fitwaffle

Pc: @kittycattykitty 🌎 I’ve never really cared about being on point with fashion.. clothes, shoes, bags, make up -  I don’t mind these things, though they've never been something I've paid too much heed to. 
But, the one thing that has truly enriched my soul over the last decade has been the spiritual journey that I’ve embarked upon through my travel experiences. Meeting new people, understanding their culture, food and interpersonal equations has given me immense joy and broadened my mental horizon ❤️ While today, the future of personal freedom and wanderlust seems to be in limbo with a weak line of sight on when this will all be over, here is a throwback to a surreal sunny day from my last summer in #London ❤ 
I sincerely hope that the world heals soon and we can all cherish and share many such experiences with each other. Until then stay home and stay safe x #stayhome #wanderlust #travelgram #traveldiaries #spiritual #summer #2019 #world #heal #instagood #instagram #igers #jantacurfew #throwback #corona #coronavirus

DE - “Any change, even a change for the better, is always accompanied by drawbacks and discomforts.” - Arnold Bennett⁣
⁣
Hast du dich auch schon einmal im Kreis gedreht und bist nicht weitergekommen? Genau dann solltest du dir überlegen, öfters Veränderungen vorzunehmen. 🌀⁣
Es ist möglich, dass einige von euch Veränderung mit etwas Negativem assoziieren. Aber auch Veränderung ist ein Fortschritt. Und große Änderungen im Leben können zwar unangenehm sein, sind aber oft auch unumgänglich. Ich kann euch aus Erfahrung sagen, dass Veränderungen in die richtige Richtung euer Leben bereichern werden - auch wenn sie nicht immer bequem sind. ✨⁣
⁣
Habt ihr auch kürzlich Veränderungen durchgemacht und Fortschritt zugelassen? ⁣
⁣
⁣
EN - “Any change, even a change for the better, is always accompanied by drawbacks and discomforts.” - Arnold Bennett⁣
⁣
Have you ever been running in circles and made no progress? Then you should consider making changes more often. 🌀⁣
Probably some of you associate change with something negative. But change is also progress. And big changes in life can be uncomfortable, but not unavoidable. I can tell from my own experiences, that changes in the right direction can enrich your life - even if they aren’t always comfortable. ✨⁣
⁣
Have you recently gone through changes and allowed progress?⁣
⁣
#progress #changes #goalsetting #mindset #business #businesstipps #businesslifestyle #businessthoughts 📷 @marthaga_

caption.text:
Our building, a Grade II listed church, has survived through tougher times than this. A local bomb 💣 map shows us that it was very lucky during WW2, getting narrowly missed by all the bombing in the immediate area! We are looking forward to getting reopen with a bang as soon as we can!

We hope you are all enjoying the start of the Easter 🐣 weekend or Passover and we’re excited to see you all again at the club as soon as it’s safe to do so. #nhsheroes 🌈🙌🏼

Almost 2000years ago, Jesus Christ paid the ultimate price by laying down his life on the cross of Calvary for mankind. Today on Good Friday, we are reminded of this great gesture and we are urged to make selfless sacrifices and love one another. As you do so, I implore you to say a prayer for my sister and all NHS/ Health Workers all over the world who are working selflessly and tirelessly doing straight shifts to save lives during this pandemic. God bless us all 🙏🏾 #sisters #goodfriday #nhs #love #appreciation
Weirdly getting used to quarantine, I wonder if I’ll miss being inside when we are allowed out again 🌻

BBALL Day 1 AKA I JUST WANNA BREAK SOME ANKLES!!! 😈 I Never Played Basketball Growing Up!! I Was Into Badminton & Chess 😂 🤷🏾‍♂️ So Since I Got All This Free Time And I’ve Dream Of Breaking People’s Ankles I’m Gonna Train To Achieve My Dreams 😂 .

📍Location: #London #UK
≕≔≕≔≕≔≕≔≕≔≕≔≕≔≕≔≕≔≕≔
#⃣ Tag your pictures with: #london_vacations

Envy at its finest.⁣
Their insecurity shining through.⁣
⁣
Remember: “Rule number one, never count your homie pockets thinkin' you deserve it.”⁣
⁣
Never have hate in your heart. Jealousy, envy and spite are evil characteristics. Ask for help, learn from others, teach yourself the game, apply knowledge, practice and adapt. Leave the rest with God. Wait for your time and stay down until you come up.⁣
⁣
You should never look at your brother envious way- that’s a flaw on your part. Be happy that others are blessed and celebrate them. Use their success as a source of motivation and inspiration. ⁣
⁣
“Envy consumes good deeds just as fire consumes wood.” - Prophet Muhammad (ﷺ)⁣

user.full_name: Y O G I  B A R E ® Yoga

caption.text:
||UPPER BODY⏫|| Grab a band in ya hands 🙌🏻 Home upper body can be tricky (particularly for pull exercises) here’s a little upper body inspo using just one resistance band (intensify as you need by making the band shorter, longer or doubling it up)
.
💪🏼 Bent over row - hinge at the hips and keep the back as straight as you can. Imagine you’re giving someone a moony 😉 (thanks @christianlewispratt for that analogy)
💪🏼Lunge with overhead W’s, try and keep the lower body as stable as possible. Think about wrapping the elbows down by the torso and squeezing the shoulder blades.
💪🏼 Push ups, can be done with or without the band, also can be done on knees. Try and keep your neck inline with the spine (easier said than done)
💪🏼 Superman reaches
💪🏼Tricep extensions - again try to keep the back straight and try not to lock out the arms all the way.
.
Add it in to your current program or try a circuit of 45 secs on 15 secs off, 2-3 rounds over.
🧗🏼‍♀️🧘🏽‍♂️⛷🏃🏼‍♀️🏄🏼‍♂️🏊🏼‍♀️🚴🏼‍♀️
Save, share & TAG us in YOUR #rockingfromhome workouts @rockandsouladventures & @kimhartwell and lets inspire one another to keep adventure strong from home!
When you’ve prepared loads of cute outfits for the summer, wear them at home, you can still feel cute.

Lucas got already into the habit of asking for his Haliborange Softies after his lunch, perfect to give him a boost when integrated into a healthy diet. caption.text:
Добрый день, мои дорогие читатели!  Сейчас, когда нет возможности вот так просто попасть в музей, предлагаю в ближайшие дни совершить увлекательные экскурсии...
Я расскажу об основателях, об экспонатах, которые вы сможете взять на заметку, а потом и увидеть, посетив тот или иной музей. 
Это будет своего рода путеводитель, который даст представления о коллекциях знаменитых музеев мира! .
Итак, предлагаю вместе со мной отправиться в Англию!
Британский музей - знаменитая достопримечательность Лондона и Великобритании. Источником его первых коллекций, как это часто происходило с музеями в Англии, чьи жители были издавна охвачены страстью к коллекционированию, стали  частные собрания, принадлежащие  сэру Хансу Слоуну. Его коллекции были чрезвычайно разнообразны. Экспонаты естественнонаучного толка соседствовали с этнографическими и археологическими редкостями, историческими реликвиями, картинами, рисунками, книгами и манускриптами. В 1753 году сэр Ханс Слоун умер, завещав свою коллекцию королю Георгию II. Этот подарок насчитывал более 70-ти тысяч античных экспонатов, среди которых было около 250-ти памятников.
.
На создание музея, учрежденного специальным актом Парламента, потребовалось 6 лет. Торжественное открытие произошло в 15 января 1759 года. Изначально музей располагался в Монтегю-Хаус, особняке XVII века, выкупленном под музей. В период с 1823 по 1847 г. Монтегю-хаус был снесён, и на его месте возведено современное здание музея, спроектированное  Робертом Смёрком в стиле неоклассики. Этот гигантский особняк располагается на одной из центральных улиц Лондона — Грейт Рассел стрит (Great Russell street) и занимает площадь более 6-ти гектаров.

Итак, в  далеком 1759 году Британский музей принял первых посетителей, которыми стали высокопоставленные особы и друзья королевской семьи. Лишь в 1847 году двери музея впервые открылись для простых людей. Современные туристы и жители Лондона сейчас имеют возможность бесплатно посещать залы музея, наблюдать уникальные экспонаты каждого из сотни залов.

preview_comments.text:
Slide 7: Step five: history and context If you are still a little stuck it can be very useful to look for inspiration in our history: we have seen many incredible visual protests from the LGBTIQ+ community in the past which can help aid our current efforts. Some good examples include the names project quilt by cleve jones silence=death by the silence death collective and queer liberation marches 
Slide 8: what next? Due to the current crisis our abilities to protest are quite severely impacted but this doesn’t mean it cannot be done. Put it online! Make art, signs and messages and get them out on social media for people to see. Make signs for yourself to affirm your identity and promote positivity. 
Slide 9: what can I do now? If you are feeling inspired then get creative and on the 24th of April upload your signs with the hashtags #queerprotestathome #stayinginbutnotsilent 
Slide 10: what can I do now? We can share eachothers messages, see our creativity and uplift us all as a community

caption.text:
✨CALL TO ACTION!✨Hello everyone! Following on from our sign making livestream, we’ve put together a quick guide to creating your own protest sign from home. Get creative and on the 24th April upload your signs with #queerprotestathome and #stayinginbutnotsilent and we can come together and share our signs and art in a form of online protest, to show the world that queer liberation matters now and always.  Graphics by @grumpy.lemon  Image descriptions (continued in comments)  Slide 1: Sign Making - A quick guide to queer sign design and crafting your own personal revolution 
Slide 2: Step one: purpose Before you begin ask yourself these questions: Who will see my sign? Who is it aimed at? Where will it be seen? These will help give you a rough guide to work with and shape your message and ideas.

Slide 3: Step two: materials Cardboard Paper Wood Fabric: Sheets, felt, cloth etc. Reuse and Recycle as much as you can! Some good decoration tools include posca paint pens acrylic paint permanent markers glitter glue keep it bold and colourful

Slide 4: Step three: message After considering the context of your sign you need a message or short phrase to display. Coming up with a message can be tricky so remember these tips: Keep it short and simple Language should be accessible It doesn’t have to sound revolutionary: just get your point across. 
Slide 5: There are 4 brightly coloured signs each saying: Intersex rights now, we’re re here we’re queer we’re not going shopping, non binary and proud and trans lives matter. Text surrounding the signs says: using protest chants can be a good place to start, easy to understand and uplifting and positive affirmations. 
Slide 6: Step four: design There are no limitations when it comes to designing how your sign looks, just remember: Be as creative as you can! Keep in mind things like legibility and sizing but don’t overthink it: your sign will be unique to go and your own design abilities

preview_comments.text: A London treasure, no visit is complete without a trip to the Burlington arcade for me !

caption.text:
"The way London just carries on in the face of everything and the way a smile to to a stranger can connect them with you without a word needing to be said. I have experienced this over the years a number of times where people just come together and carry on. I suppose it’s the small little things that shows the place the arcade holds in so many people’s lives." - Mark Lord, Head Beadle⁠

This Bank Holiday weekend would have been the 32nd anniversary of The London International Ska Festival. I would be lying if I said that we aren’t gutted it's not taking place. With the weather set fair, ordinarily we’d be welcoming revellers from all over the world, beaming happy faces walking into our Camden store, customers from previous years we’ve served & then bumped into on dance floors, shared a beer with and got to know at the many & varied events that make this festival so very special. 
Those interactions wouldn’t have been possible without one man’s vision, hard work and passion for the music, our good friend Mr Sean Flowerdew. Who back in 1988 borrowed £500 from his mum to put on a London based festival showcasing just how strong the Ska scene was in London at the time. 
He’s someone who keeps a relatively low profile, but has managed to put legendary Jamaican originators on London stages from day one, having both Rodigan and Coxsone DJ events that we've attended, while keeping his finger on the pulse of what’s fresh and current in all things Ska, Dub & Lovers Rock. 
Instagram isn’t the place to tell you the full story of the Ska Festival, but jump over to our Facebook page for a more in-depth history & an interview with the man himself.
Here’s some good news....
Whether you're looking forward to joining 600 partygoers on the Thames as you board The Dixie Queen with Tower Bridge opening to the sound of The Pioneers, or skanking the night away at The Islington Academy, The London International Ska Festival 2020 is going to happen - in fact the rescheduled dates have been confirmed for August 28th - 30th.
From all of us at Modfather Clothing, we’re counting down the days. We can’t wait to see some of those familiar faces that are in our thoughts this weekend.

Stay Safe, turn up the volume & enjoy Sean Flowerdew’s playlist for Modfather Clothing.

caption.text:
This is my new eBay skirt. Originally from @zara - it pretty much ticks every box. It’s long enough for a tallish person, it’s a beautiful colour - a peachy/dusky/tan nude - and most of all it lets me swish around in a kind of dream state. In my own beautiful world where Italian light hits a bowl of freshly picked figs, where the sound of friends and lovers talking and laughing drifts by on the warm summery night air. Where someone somewhere is playing a piano from behind an open window. Where children draw intently in chalk on pathways and create spontaneous games into the twilight. All this in a skirt. That’s a little glimpse of my interior world. - a lot goes on when I let it carry me away. Tell me about your interior worlds, and what takes you there? Please let’s share inspiration at this time where we can’t travel or see friends and family. Pretty pretty please 🙏🏻 .
.

Join us every Thursday at 2 p.m. BST on Zoom as we bring great minds and creative activists together to share their wisdom 🎙

Connecting with the inner strength of basic goodness. As we cultivate our garden, the conditions become more conducive to the growth of bodhichitta (mind that strives toward awakening, empathy, and compassion for the benefit of all sentient beings.) The joy comes from not giving up on ourselves, from mindfully sticking with ourselves and beginning to experience our great warrior spirit. We also provide the conditions for joy to expand by training in the practices of the heart, and in particular by training in rejoicing and appreciation. Love and gratitude  Sat Nam xx

caption.text:
SKINCARE ROUTINE - Here is a video I recorded a while ago and uploaded on Tiktok but I thought it would be great to post on insta too! My skin has improved so much since then Alhumdulilah ❤️ this routine works great for me!
———
So little facts about my skin, I suffer from Keratosis Pilaris and Rosacea. My skin is naturally quite red and my cheeks look like I have a rash on them when it’s just my skin (it is prominent when i apply my skincare products so you will gradually see that my face is getting more and more red but this is normal for me). These conditions have no cure but I’ve learnt to accept it! Nobody is perfect and if other people suffer from the same thing, I feel you! I feel beautiful in my skin and that’s all that matters - perfection is overrated. ❤️💯
————
Products:
- @tatcha deep cleanse face wash.
- Rose water as toner (soothes the skin).
- @tatcha essence.
- @olehenriksen truth serum.
- @olehenriksen brightening cream.
- @tatcha water cream.
- @olehenriksen banana bright eye cream.
- Rosehip oil to fade scarring from @hollandandbarrett - @facegym jade stone for lymphatic drainage.
- Lip exfoliator from Amazon. - @ctilburymakeup Night cream for dry areas.
- @originsuk spot gel (I apply this before moisturiser now! Thanks to @aminathepharmacist) works way better.
————

caption.text:
Hello everyone!! Today's video is brought to you by @stump_kitchen and her wonderful video for @cbckidsca where she demonstrates how to wash her hands 😁

People always ask me "how can you wash your hands?" And I would like to demonstrate how I wash mine as a short below elbow lucky fin 😊 Elara is just happy to be in the video lol. Have you ever gotten this question?

#limbdifferenceawarenessmonth #limblossawarenessmonth #luckyfinproject #luckyfin #amputeelife #amputeegirl #amnioticbandsyndrome #abs #limbdifference #momlifebelike

Με τον Γουόρχολ σε 12 αίθουσες

Μπορεί η μεγάλη αναδρομική έκθεση για τον Αντι Γουόρχολ, που ατυχώς είχε προγραμματιστεί να ανοίξει στις 12 Μαρτίου, να παραμένει κλειστή για το κοινό, αλλά η Tate Modern του Λονδίνου προσφέρει μια θαυμάσια διαδικτυακή περιήγηση (tate.org.uk). Πριν κλείσει η γκαλερί, μερικά από τα σημαντικότερα –τα  πιο «αγαπημένα» τους, λένε οι άνθρωποι της Τate– σημεία και έργα της έκθεσης βιντεοσκοπήθηκαν, και από σήμερα τα μοιράζονται μαζί μας με ένα βίντεο διάρκειας 7 λεπτών που διαθέτει αγγλικούς υπότιτλους. Με ωραίες λήψεις, μουσική, μοντάζ και ενδιαφέρουσες πληροφορίες από τους δύο επιμελητές της έκθεσης, η γκαλερί μας βάζει πραγματικά μέσα στον κόσμο του Γουόρχολ, εξερευνώντας τη ζωή και τη δημιουργία του σε 12 αίθουσες.

Οι επιμελητές μάς συστήνουν όχι μόνον έναν σούπερ σταρ της pop art, αλλά έναν καλλιτέχνη που επαναπροσδιόρισε το νόημα της τέχνης σε μια εποχή μεγάλων κοινωνικών, πολιτικών και τεχνολογικών αλλαγών. Μια πολύ καλή ευκαιρία να επιστρέψουμε σε άλλες, πιο χαλαρές δεκαετίες και παράλληλα να ακούσουμε φρέσκες σκέψεις για έναν πολύπλευρο δημιουργό.

Άρθρο της @kathimerini : https://www.kathimerini.gr/1072889/article/politismos/eikastika/me-ton-goyorxol-se-12-ai8oyses

Leftovers 🥘.. how long can you safly keep leftovers?? 🤔
.
.
📌You can keep leftovers in the refrigerator for 3-4 days. 3-4 months in the freezer. For safety reasons and also to preserve the flavors & taste of food, wrap your leftovers or put them in a sealed container. .
.
📌To thaw leftovers: leave them in the refrigerator, or on a cold water, or use microwave thawing. All are safe. .
.
📌Can I re- freeze leftover leftovers❓Yes, if you have a big leftover quantity & you consumed only a portion from it, you still can safely refreeze the left leftover, after heating it to 160F (use a food thermometer 🌡 ) .
.
📌Consume your thawed frozen leftovers within 3-4 days. .
.
.
💚I personally prefer to consume all leftovers within two days, as the taste & freshness of the food decreases with refrigeration.
.
.
.
💚 Stay Safe , Stay Positive 💚
.
.
.
.
.

Alternating between 20-second intervals of intense work and 10-second intervals of rest. After you do 8 intervals of each move onto the next exercise. Follow this pattern—20 seconds of work, 10 seconds of rest, 8 times—for each exercise on the list.

A1: Tabata slide —20 seconds
* Rest—10 seconds
* Do 8 times.
B1: Standing knee drives —20 seconds
* Rest—10 seconds
* Do 8 times.
C1: Russian Twist —20 seconds
* Rest—10 seconds
* Do 8 times.
D1: Step outs —20 seconds
* Rest—10 seconds
* Do 8 times.
E1: Crab Reach —20 seconds
* Rest—10 seconds
* Do 8 times.
